    "from collections import defaultdict\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from rdkit import Chem\n",
    "from IPython.display import SVG\n",
    "\n",
    "import openpharmacophore as oph"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We want to get ligand based pharmacophores for thrombin. \n",
    "\n",
    "We'll start by loading a set pf thrombin ligands and generating conformers for each. Then we will\n",
    "store the conformers on a file to avoid needing to generate new conformers each time the notebooks is ran."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,

   "source": [
    "lig_df = pd.read_csv(\"../data/thrombin.csv\")\n",
    "lig_df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def load_ligands():\n",
    "    smiles = lig_df[\"Smiles\"].tolist()\n",
    "    return oph.load_ligands(smiles, form=\"smi\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "conf_file = \"../data/thrombin_ligands.sdf\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Number of conformers  [176, 174, 166, 147, 176, 40, 286]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "if not os.path.isfile(conf_file):\n",
    "    ligands = load_ligands()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    ligands = oph.load(conf_file)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Number of conformers \", [l.n_conformers for l in ligands])\n",
    "oph.draw_ligands(ligands, n_per_row=4, legends=[l.to_rdkit().GetProp(\"_Name\") for l in ligands])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we generate conformers for each ligand. The argument n_confs is set to -1 so that the conformer generator\n",
    "creates and \"ideal\" number of conformers for each ligand."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for lig in ligands:\n",
    "    if not lig.has_conformers:\n",
    "        lig.add_hydrogens()\n",
    "        lig.generate_conformers(n_confs=-1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ligand 0 has 176 conformers\n",
      "Ligand 1 has 174 conformers\n",
      "Ligand 2 has 166 conformers\n",
      "Ligand 3 has 147 conformers\n",
      "Ligand 4 has 176 conformers\n",
      "Ligand 5 has 40 conformers\n",
      "Ligand 6 has 286 conformers\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for ii, lig in enumerate(ligands):\n",
    "    print(f\"Ligand {ii} has {lig.n_conformers} conformers\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Save conformers to file\n",
    "if not os.path.isfile(conf_file):\n",
    "    writer = Chem.SDWriter(conf_file)\n",
    "    for lig in ligands:\n",
    "        lig_rdkit = lig.to_rdkit()\n",
    "        for conf in range(lig.n_conformers):\n",
    "            writer.write(lig_rdkit, confId=conf)\n",
    "    writer.close()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Analyizing chem feats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def chem_feats_df():\n",
    "    n_feats = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "    names = []\n",
    "    for lig in ligands:\n",
    "        names.append(lig.to_rdkit().GetProp(\"_Name\"))\n",
    "        for feat_type, ind_list in lig.feat_ind.items():\n",
    "            n_feats[feat_type].append(len(ind_list))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(n_feats)\n",
    "    df[\"ligand\"] = names\n",
    "    df.set_index(\"ligand\", drop=True, inplace=True)\n",
    "    df[\"total\"] = df.sum(axis=1)\n",
    "    return df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for lig in ligands:\n",
    "    lig.get_chem_feats(0)"
   ]

    "## Finding common pharmacophores"
   ]

   "source": [
    "pharma_file = \"../data/thrombin_pharmacophores.mol2\""
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import time\n",

    "start = time.time()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Found 63 pharmacopohores\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_points = [3, 4, 5, 6]\n",
    "min_actives = [4, 5, 6]\n",
    "\n",
    "if not os.path.isfile(pharma_file):\n",
    "\n",
    "    pharmacophores = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    for ii in range(len(n_points)):\n",
    "        for jj in range(len(min_actives)):        \n",
    "            pnts = n_points[ii]\n",
    "            actives = min_actives[jj]\n",
    "\n",
    "            pharma = oph.LigandBasedPharmacophore(ligands)\n",
    "            pharma.extract(\n",
    "                    n_points=pnts, min_actives=actives, max_pharmacophores=10\n",
    "            )\n",
    "\n",
    "            print(f\"Num points: {pnts}. Min actives: {actives}. Found {len(pharma)} pharmacophores\")\n",
    "            if len(pharma) > 0:\n",
    "                for p in pharma.pharmacophores:\n",
    "                    p.props[\"min_actives\"] = actives\n",
    "                pharmacophores.extend(pharma.pharmacophores)\n",
    "\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    pharmacophores = oph.pharmacophore_reader.read_mol2(pharma_file)\n",
    "    \n",
    "print(f\"Found {len(pharmacophores)} pharmacopohores\")"
   ]
  },

   "source": [

    "if not os.path.isfile(pharma_file):\n",

    "def pharmacophore_df():\n",
    "    \n",
    "    rows = {}\n",
    "    ii = 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for pharma in pharmacophores: \n",
    "        feat_str = \"\"\n",
    "        # Only add the top scoring pharmacophore\n",
    "        for point in pharma:\n",
    "            feat_str += point.short_name\n",
    "            \n",
    "        n_pnts = len(pharma)\n",
    "        n_actives = int(pharma.props[\"min_actives\"])\n",
    "        rows[ii] = [n_pnts, n_actives, feat_str, pharma.ref_mol, pharma.score]\n",
    "        ii += 1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(\n",
    "        rows, \n",
    "        orient=\"index\",\n",
    "        columns=[\"Number of points\", \"Number of actives\", \"Features\", \"Reference ligand\", \"Score\"]\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return df"
   ]

    "def generate_image():\n",
